## Commit Messages
- Use: "type(scope): desc"
- Use a maximum of 50 including type and scope for title.
- Use a maximum of 72 characters for subsequent lines, then wrap the line.
- Include bullet points describing the changes in the commit to support the short description.
- Use the following types:
  - feat: A new feature
  - fix: A bug fix
  - docs: Documentation changes
  - style: Code style changes (formatting, missing semicolons, etc.)
  - refactor: Code changes that neither fix a bug nor add a feature
  - perf: Performance improvements
  - test: Adding or updating tests
  - chore: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries such as documentation generation
  - ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
  - build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
- Example:
```
feat(config): keep this short

- be explicit here
- and here
```